This paper deals with the analysis of political polarization and its impact on the spread of misinformation on social media. It involves the use of natural language processing techniques to analyze tweets and URLs associated with fake news. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
